-- Cameroon’s Average Cocoa Export Price Climbed 0.6% Last Week
-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 2012-03-21T06:18:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/cameroon-s-average-cocoa-export-price-climbed-0-6-last-week.html
Cameroon’s average cocoa export
price at the main port of Douala rose 0.6 percent to 1,078  CFA
francs  per kilogram (2.2 pounds) in the week to March 19,
according to Bloomberg calculation from daily data sent by the
Cocoa and Coffee Board through mobile-phone text message.  The Central African nation, the continent’s fourth-biggest
producer of the crop, exported 149,792 metric tons of cocoa
since the season started in August, the board said on Feb. 21.  The following is a table of exports rates (free on board)
at the port in CFA francs per kilogram.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pius Lukong in Yaounde via Nairobi at 
